The `console.log` needs to be inside the event listener callback. With the `console.log` outside, it runs once immediately. The event listener callback is invoked whenever the input changes. With the `console.log` inside, it will log the value every time it changes.

If you need to do something specific with the `stat` value when it changes, that logic should live in the event callback function.

